# Persona Studio — UI rules

- **One component set, two families.** Differ via `data-studio-theme` +
  `--persona-accent` and CSS variables. Never fork the layout per family.
- Editorial, spacious, presentation-ready. Avoid dashboard chrome, tiny cards,
  dense tables, random gradients and AI-sparkle overload.
- **Accessibility (WCAG AA):** never communicate evidence status or confidence
  with colour alone — always include an icon + text label. Keyboard-navigable,
  visible focus states, semantic HTML, reduced-motion friendly.
- Consume tokens: `var(--studio-ink|paper|panel|muted|line|accent)`. Use the
  shared components in `components/persona-studio/shared` (ConfidenceBadge,
  EvidenceTag, CoverageMeter, StatementList, SectionCard).
